    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-09-20T22:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-09-20T22:00:00-05:00" n="208"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d208">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.114/175</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-09-21T11:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 21, 1918, 11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>In pursuance of your telegram September 7, 6 p.m. I have consulted with British
                    Minister who advised me that he was without instructions in the matter but that
                    he would telegraph his Government that by your direction I had approached him on
                    the subject. I have addressed to the Minister of Foreign Affairs a separate
                    protest against opium transaction in the sense of your telegram cited.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
